<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-09-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-09-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="836" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d836">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">836.48 1930 Hurricane/9: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Hoover</persName> to
                                President <persName type="to">Trujillo</persName></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-09-04">September 4, 1930</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I am shocked and grieved to learn of the terrible storm disaster which
                            has wrought such devastation in Santo Domingo and I hasten to send you
                            my own deep sympathy and that of my fellow citizens with your suffering
                            people.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Herbert Hoover</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>